The authorities of Obafemi Awolowo University, OAU, Ile-Ife has confirmed the release of a lecturer, Professor Olayinka Adegbehingbe, who was kidnapped by unidentified gunmen on Sunday evening. The Public Relations Officer of the university, Mr Abiodun Olanrewaju confirmed that the professor had regained his freedom. Olanrewaju said “the University Management hereby express her appreciation to the general public for their support, love and concerns.” OAU management also thanked the officers and men of the Osun State Command of the Nigeria Police, particularly the Police Commissioner, for their prompt response and professionalism. Buhari’s spokesman, Adesina loses sister Ooni of Ife to intervene in OAU crisis Ooni of Ife wades into OAU/students’ crisis Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin